article.headline: Oklahoma 89, Texas-Arlington 60
article.story: NORMAN, Okla. (AP) -- Tony Crocker scored 18 points to lead four Oklahoma players in double-figures as the Sooners defeated Texas-Arlington 89-60 in non-conference play Saturday night. Michael Neal had 17 points, while Longar Longar and Austin Johnson added 16 and 13 points respectively, to help the Sooners (6-3). Taylor Griffin added career-highs in rebounds (13) and assists (7). Texas-Arlington (3-5) was led by Brandon Long's career-best 22-point performance. Oklahoma trailed early thanks to the first of Long's six 3-pointers, but a Crocker 3-pointer gave the Sooners the lead for good at the 16:13 mark. Johnson then capped a 15-5 run with another 3-pointer that put the Sooners in front 20-10 with just minutes left in the half. Long did his best to keep the Mavericks within striking distance, connecting on consecutive treys, the latter cutting the lead to 23-18 with 9:27 left before intermission. But a 3-point play from Longar and back-to-back buckets by Johnson and Crocker kept the Mavericks on their heels. OU finished the half with a decisive 20-8 run that built the lead to 43-26 at the break. Oklahoma forced 19 turnovers and limited Texas-Arlington to 37 percent shooting from the field. The Sooners blocked a season-high eight shots, including a career-high five by Longar. Oklahoma also dominated the boards by a 48-26 margin. Neal scored only two first-half points, but dished out five assists and produced three steals. He connected on 5 of 7 shots in the second half and finished with five steals, six assists and five rebounds. Jermaine Griffin was the only other Maverick in double-figures, as he added 10 points and a team-high six rebounds.
